      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_OhioU_1829-10-14_page01.jpg"/>
            <p>
               <note place="bottom">
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>
                  <lb/>
                  <hi rend="underline">Autograph</hi>
               </note>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SingT1">
                  <roleName>Archdeacon</roleName> Singleton</persName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_OhioU_1829-10-14_page02.jpg"/>
            <p><!-- Begin transcibing the body of the letter here. -->
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName> is afraid she<lb/>
               is trespassing too frequently<lb/>
               upon <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SingT1">
                  <roleName>Archdeacon</roleName> Singleton</persName>
               <unclear>'s</unclear>
               <lb/>
               politeness and most obliging<lb/>
               offer to frank packets for<lb/>
               her - The Enclosed is a <choice>
                  <orig>mat<lb/>
               ter</orig>
                  <reg>matter</reg>
               </choice> of business of some <choice>
                  <orig>conse-<lb/>
               quence</orig>
                  <reg>consequence</reg>
               </choice> &amp; she ventures to<lb/>
               beg he will have the goodness<lb/>
               to forward it and not to be<lb/>
               quite out of patience with her<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/tgn/1042937">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
               <lb/>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>
                  <date when="1816-08-04"/>Oct 14<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1829 </dateline>
            </closer>
         </div>
